        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #31b6f0;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">You can manually edit the keyframes to change their position, timing, and transition type. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Objects/Keyframes/Editing_Keyframes.htm" >Editing Keyframes</MadCap:xref>.</p>
        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #31b6f0;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">When you automatically add cursors to a recorded movie, Mimic automatically adds opacity keyframes to the timeline, as well. These keyframes change the color of the circle around the cursor. If desired, you can move and edit these keyframes using the same process as you used to move and edit the cursor's position keyframes.</p>
